b_i
i=1,2,3
2R\sin\theta_i=b_i
 b_1+b_2-b_3=8R\sin\frac{\theta_1}{2}\sin\frac{\theta_2}{2}\cos\frac{\theta_3}{2}. 
b_1=r(\cot\frac{\theta_2}{2}+\cot\frac{\theta_3}{2})
 r\cos\frac{\theta_1}{2}=b_1\sin\frac{\theta_3}{2}\sin\frac{\theta_2}{2}. (1) 
 r\sin{\theta_1}=2b_1\sin\frac{\theta_3}{2}\sin\frac{\theta_2}{2}\sin\frac{\theta_1}{2}. 
 \frac{r}{4R}=\sin\frac{\theta_3}{2}\sin\frac{\theta_2}{2}\sin\frac{\theta_1}{2}. 
 \frac{b_1b_2b_3}{16rR^2}=\cos\frac{\theta_3}{2}\cos\frac{\theta_2}{2}\cos\frac{\theta_1}{2}. 
